  "translations": {
    "en": "The believer sees a dream and it comes to pass as he saw it, and sometimes he sees a dream but it amounts to nothing? So he said: Indeed, when the believer sleeps, an extended movement emerges from his spirit, ascending toward the heaven. So whatever the spirit of the believer sees in the kingdom of the heaven, in the place of Divine decree and regulation, that is the truth. And whatever he sees on the earth, those are confused dreams.",
